    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The system sends this notification when the setting for head-anchored content changes.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "When you receive this notification, call ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.Accessibility/documentation/Accessibility/AccessibilitySettings/prefersHeadAnchorAlternative",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to get",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the new setting.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "On Apple Vision Pro, apps can create a heads-up display effect by setting up content",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to follow the person’s head position. This effect allows the content to remain in",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the same position, no matter where the person looks. However, some assistive technologies",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "are incompatible with this type of content. For example, a technology might use the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "person’s head movements to control the current selection, or they might magnify content",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to make it easier to read. Anchoring content to the head position prevents these",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "technologies from interacting with that content.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
